#KEY "*magincia*" {
      "Magincia is an island city east of Britain.",
      "Magincia, they say, would be food for pirates were it not for Moonglow's magic.",
      "Ach! Magincia is all flash and glitter! Too much money, not enough sense.",
      "I heard that the most common shop in Magincia has more gems than Lord British' crown!",
      "They have everything in Magincia, save common sense.",
      "Magincia! Lazy ... overindulged ... spoilt rotten ...richling peasants! Dost not get me started!",
      "I heard that the floors in Magincia clean themselves. Now that's something I'd like to have!",
      "They use magic in Magincia to keep from doing work. Seems like cheating to me.",
      "There's not much farm land near Magincia, that much I can tell thee. They'd rather pay to have food brought to them.",
      "They'd not let the likes of us live in Magincia. 'Tis a city with only ladies, no ladies-in-waiting.",
      "I think they have a diamond mine in Magincia.",
      "They are lucky to have magical protection in Magincia. Not a city cares for them, and people hereabouts would like to teach them manners.",
      "Someone told me that the fine lords and ladies in Magincia hire peasants to talk to peasants. Keeps them a bit father away from the common riffraff, I suppose.",
      "It's said that in Magincia, they'd rather look good than feel good.",
      "The main difference between someone from Magincia and a peasant is that the Magincian is NOT a PEASANT! If thou see'est what I mean.",
      "They produce nothing in Magincia but snobs and money.",
      "Someday they'll run out of diamonds in Magincia, and with hunger will come wisdom and compassion.",
      "Magincia is a land of over-plenty and overmuch pride. "
    }
#KEY "*yew*" {
